    <note>
        <div>
            <p>The Bureau of German Affairs was organized on Nov 1, 1949, superseding the Office of
                German and Austrian Affairs. Its Director held rank equivalent to an Assistant
                Secretary of State. The first incumbent was commissioned by the President and the
                second designated by the Secretary of State. The Bureau was abolished and its
                functions transferred to the Bureau of European Affairs on Nov 2, 1953.</p>
        </div>
    </note>
